<https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/the-pensions-regulator> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "The Pensions Regulator (TPR) is the UK regulator of work-based pension schemes. It works with trustees, employers, pension specialists and business advisers, giving guidance on what is expected of them. TPR is an executive non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Department for Work and Pensions ."@en .
